  "summary": "onboardconnect-agent posts environment data to attacker-controlled Cloudflare Worker at install time",
  "details": "The package's setup script (dist/setup.js) performs an HTTP POST to https://oc-worker-tenant-api.wpolanco.workers.dev carrying values read from process.env, with additional fetch() calls in the same file. Further POST sinks are present in dist/server.js (lines 40, 221, 225, 230, 235) alongside a ping invocation at line 509, and base64 decoding paths appear in dist/crypto.js and dist/store.js consistent with payload staging or credential handling. The destination is a personal *.workers.dev subdomain (\"wpolanco\"), not a vendor or publisher-aligned host, and there is no documented purpose for an agent package to relay environment variables to a third-party Cloudflare Worker. This shape — install/setup-time fetch + process.env read + hardcoded non-publisher endpoint — is the exfiltration fingerprint described in the hardcoded-C2 calibration.",
